3:Ta13,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Can international students study in Nepal without knowing Nepali?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Many programs accept international students through English-medium instruction, but language requirements vary by institution and field."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which documents are usually required for admission?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most applications ask for transcripts, passport copy, photos, and a statement of purpose. Some programs may ask for extra academic or language documents."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much should I budget for tuition and living costs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Costs vary by institution, city, and study level. Nepal is generally more affordable than many destinations, but exact numbers should be checked per program."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is a student visa needed to study in Nepal?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, international students typically need a student visa or equivalent permit. Requirements can change, so applicants should verify with the institution and authorities."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are scholarships available?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Some universities and colleges offer fee reductions, merit-based support, or targeted scholarships, but availability is limited and competitive."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is student life like in Kathmandu and other cities?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Kathmandu offers the largest concentration of institutions and services, while cities like Pokhara provide a calmer setting with strong lifestyle appeal."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I work while studying?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Work rules depend on the institution, visa status, and local regulations. Students should confirm permissions before planning any work."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I choose between a university and a college?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Universities can suit broader academic goals, while colleges can be a better fit for specific programs, cost management, or a more focused study path."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What careers are strongest after studying in Nepal?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Business, IT, hospitality, health, and education programs often connect well to employability, but the best option depends on your profile and goals."}}],"url":"https://studyinnepal.com/why-study-nepal"}0:["ffv6yAbLyuvkU28pHDtQ-",[[["",{"children":["why-study-nepal",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["why-study-nepal",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",["$","main",null,{"className":"mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8","children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] border border-[rgba(15,42,95,0.12)] bg-[linear-gradient(140deg,#081a3a_0%,#0f2a5f_50%,#143b7c_100%)] p-7 text-white shadow-[0_24px_70px_rgba(8,26,58,0.2)] sm:p-10","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.32em] text-white/70","children":"Why Study in Nepal"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"mt-4 max-w-3xl text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight sm:text-5xl","children":"Experience top-notch education, vibrant culture, and limitless possibilities in one of South Asia\\'s fastest-growing education destinations."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-5 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-7 text-white/80 sm:text-base","children":"Start with clear information, trusted institutions, and practical planning support for your next academic step in Nepal."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/booking","className":"inline-flex rounded-full bg-white px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-primary)] transition hover:bg-[rgba(255,255,255,0.92)] focus-ring","children